\n\n<p>There are a different types of maintenance namely, breakdown maintenance, corrective maintenance, preventive maintenance, and condition-based maintenance which can be carried out depending on the situation of things. Regardless of whatever maintenance is needed, the main objective of an efficient maintenance schedule is to manage downtime and its impact on the production process in an industry. For instance, efficient preventative maintenance in an industry such as industrial wastewater plants is carried out on lift stations, air release valves (ARV\u2019s), head works structures aeration equipment, and return &amp; waste sludge pumps with digestion aeration equipment.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Every industrial wastewater plant facility requires a specific approach to how maintenance should be undertaken. Some other factors influence the preventive maintenance program and its success such as the skill level of the maintenance personnel, the complexity of the equipment and where the equipment is being used. During the maintenance proper documentation of equipment, deterioration should be done. This information will enable you to plan on when to replace or repairs parts of the wastewater plants before they cause system process failure.\u00a0 Partial or complete overhauls should occur weekly, monthly, quarterly or annually.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>An efficient maintenance schedule objective is to:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li>Increase functionality reliability of production facilities.<\/li><li>Maximize life of equipment.<\/li><li>Maximize production capacity.<\/li><li>Achieve quality product or services by well operated equipment.<\/li><li>Minimize interruptions in operations.<\/li><li>Minimize breakdowns.<\/li><li>Enhance manpower safety.<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Regardless of how intensive your process may be, sooner or later a piece of equipment will break down.\u00a0 Once an efficient maintenance schedule is carried out, you can be well assured that the life span of your equipment will be longer and breakdowns will be minimized.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/lejiccal.com\/\" title=\"Emobella Engineering\">Emobella Engineering<\/a> is an industry-leading professional service in providing preventive maintenance, repair, and calibration for Industrial and Waste Water Treatment Plants.\u00a0 Our technicians have been trained by the manufacturer to help you pass your inspection, documentation and certification.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you are interested, have any questions, or would like to get more information on any of the following information provided for Preventive Maintenance of Industrial Waste Water Treatment Plants, please contact us <a href=\"http:\/\/bit.ly\/CONTACTEMOBELLA\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"contact us\">http:\/\/bit.ly\/CONTACTEMOBELLA <\/a>\u00a0<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>There are a different types of maintenance namely, breakdown maintenance, corrective maintenance, preventive maintenance, and condition-based maintenance which can be carried out depending on the situation of things. Regardless of whatever maintenance is needed, the main objective of an efficient maintenance schedule is to manage downtime and its impact on the production process in an &hellip;<\/p>\n<p class=\"read-more\"> <a class=\"\" href=\"https:\/\/lejiccal.com\/efficient-maintenance-schedule-on-industrial-waste-water-plant\/\"> <span class=\"screen-reader-text\">Efficient Maintenance Schedule on Industrial Waste Water Plant<\/span> Read More &raquo;<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":4536,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"om_disable_all_campaigns":false,"_mi_skip_tracking":false,"_monsterinsights_sitenote_active":false,"_monsterinsights_sitenote_note":"","_monsterinsights_sitenote_category":0,"site-sidebar-layout":"default","site-content-layout":"default","ast-global-header-display":